N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 1 ยง 20.17 - Filled milk

State Regulations

Filled milk means any combination of nonmilk fat (or oil)
with skim milk (whether fresh, cultured, reconstituted or modified by the
addition of nonfat milk solids), with or without milkfat, so that the product
(including stabilizers, emulsifiers or flavoring) resembles milk or any other
fluid milk product; and contains less than 6 percent nonmilk fat (or
oil). Notes
